mustMatchAny.description: A list of filters representing disjunctions of conjunctive simple filters. The implementation is currently limited to 1 level of nesting. E.g. `(a AND b AND NOT c) OR (d AND e) OR (f AND g)` is supported, but `(a OR (b OR c))` is not supported. The latter should be expressed as `(a OR b OR c)`. `(a AND (b OR c))` is also not supported. Mutually exclusive with `mustMatchRegexes` and `mustNotMatchRegexes`.

mustMatchRegexes.description: An attribute must match all of the regexes from the list to be returned. Mutually exclusive with `mustMatchAny`

mustNotMatchRegexes.description: An attribute must match none of the regexes from the list to be returned. Mutually exclusive with `mustMatchAny`

attributePathsFilter.description: Filter attribute paths, if null api returns all attributes

limit.description: Results limit, can be null on request (default applied)

nextPageToken.description: Next page token, can be null (first requested / last returned page)

attributeFilter.description: Filter by attribute (match any), if null no type or property value filtering is applied

attributeNameRegex.description: Filter by attribute name with regex, if null no name filtering is applied; deprecated, use attributeNameFilter instead; if attributeNameFilter is set, this field is ignored

experimentIdsFilter.description: Filter by experiment id, if null all experiments are considered

attributeNamesFilter.description: Filter by attribute name, if null all attributes are considered
